titleInfo.title: Henderson v. Houston
titleInfo.subTitle: MEMORANDUM AND ORDER-This matter is before the court on Respondent's Motion for Summary Judgment. IT IS THEREFORE ORDERED that: Respondent's Motion for Summary Judgment (filing no. 12) is denied without prejudice to reassertion. Respondent shall file an answer and separate brief no later than 30 days from the date of this Memorandum and Order. No later than 30 days following the filing of Respondent's brief, Petitioner shall file and serve a brief in response. No later than 30 days after the filing of Petitioner's brief, Respondent shall file and serve a reply brief. Petitioner's Motion for Additional State Court Records (filing no. 14) is denied without prejudice to reassertion after Respondents submission of state court records as set forth above. Ordered by Judge Richard G. Kopf. (Copy mailed to pro se party)(LKH)
